headline: MAA Net Profit Margin Surpasses Expectations but One-Off Gain Challenges Earnings Quality Narrative
summary: Mid-America Apartment Communities (MAA) booked net profit margins of 25.1%, up from last year’s 23.7%. The company recorded a five-year average annual earnings growth of 8.6%, though growth slowed to 6.7% in the most recent year. Looking ahead, analysts expect earnings to shrink by 5% per year over the next three years. Revenue is forecast to grow at 4.7% annually, trailing the broader US market's 10.3% projected pace. These results reflect steady historical profitability but raise questions...
